      "message": "[warning] Line 1551: `rearmFallbackClone` is invoked once per member that fails to resolve a device, but `fallbackClone` (lines 1535-1537) fans out over *all* members, each launching an independent `forEachDevice` with its own `found` flag and `end` callback. When a conversation has several members without a currently-online device, each of their `end` callbacks calls `rearmFallbackClone`, so `fallbackTimer *\u003d 2` runs multiple times within a single fallback round (e.g. 5s→10s→20s→40s for 3 deviceless members) and `expires_at`/`async_wait` are churned repeatedly on the shared timer. This makes the exponential backoff grow per-member instead of per-round, pushing the retry interval toward MAX_FALLBACK (12h) far faster than intended and delaying eventual clones. Consider doubling/re-arming at most once per fallback round — e.g. move the backoff bump into `fallbackClone` itself (once, after dispatching all members) rather than into each device-resolution `end` callback, or guard the timer so a re-arm already scheduled this round is not doubled again.",
